The source under src/ and the integration test under t/ originate from the
upstream module above. Changes made in this project relative to upstream:

  - Renamed all source files, internal symbols, and directives from the
    ngx_http_rate_limit_* / rate_limit* naming to the single-layer
    ngx_http_ratelimit_* / ratelimit* naming.
  - Migrated the Redis command layer from RATER.LIMIT to Lua EVALSHA/EVAL
    (with a NOSCRIPT fallback).
  - Redesigned the directives into a limit_req-style named-zone model
    (ratelimit_zone + ratelimit zone=); zones carry rate semantics only and
    allocate no shared memory (the counter lives in Redis).
  - Added AUTH/SELECT connection initialization, pipelined ahead of every
    rate check (ratelimit_password / ratelimit_database).
  - Fixed a heap-buffer-overflow in the key-prefix concatenation inherited
    from upstream (ngx_cpystrn over-read of the non-NUL-terminated key).
  - Adapted t/sanity.t to the EVALSHA semantics and zone directives.

